# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AI Labor Market Simulation — environment configuration
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to ".env" (no extension prefix) and fill in any
# keys you have. The backend auto-loads .env at startup.
# Lines starting with # are comments. Everything is optional —
# anything left blank just disables that feature.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Groq cloud LLM (recommended — free, fast, varies each run) ──
# Get a free key at https://console.groq.com/keys (no credit card).
# When set, the "Groq LLM" option in the Validation page works out
# of the box for anyone running this project.
GROQ_API_KEY=
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# ── Ollama local LLM (optional) ──────────────────────────────────
# Only needed if you want to use a locally-installed Ollama model.
OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=kimi-k2.6:cloud
